==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redbreast
<hw>Red"breast`</hw> <pr>(-br?st`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The European robin.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The American robin. See <er>Robin</er>.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>The knot, or red-breasted snipe; -- called also
<altname>robin breast</altname>, and <altname>robin snipe</altname>. See
<er>Knot</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The long-eared pondfish. See
<er>Pondfish</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redbud</ent>⟦br⟧
